{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01H4soKhs27bnekZkPVgb6LY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DuzWWPQWd4vAfBBMcjKycN","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"theorem_title":"Full Glassey blow-up proof","theorem_statement":"Consider a sufficiently regular solution \(u(t,x)\) to the focusing mass-critical NLS on \(\mathbb{R}^d\):\n\[\ni\partial_t u+\Delta u=-|u|^{4/d}u.\n\]\nAssume \(u_0\in H^1(\mathbb{R}^d)\), \(|x|u_0\in L^2(\mathbb{R}^d)\), and the energy\n\[\nE(u_0)=\frac{1}{2}\int_{\mathbb{R}^d}|\nabla u_0|^2\,dx-\frac{1}{2+4/d}\int_{\mathbb{R}^d}|u_0|^{2+4/d}\,dx<0.\n\]\nThen the maximal forward existence time \(T\) is finite and \(\|u(t)\|_{H^1(\mathbb{R}^d)}\to\infty\) as \(t\uparrow T\).","root_node_id":"root","nodes":"[
  {
    "id": "root",
    "title": "Full Glassey Blow-up Theorem",
    "informal_statement": "Under the hypotheses \(u_0\in H^1\), \(|x|u_0\in L^2\), and \(E(u_0)<0\), the focusing mass-critical NLS solution blows up in finite forward time with \(\|u(t)\|_{H^1}\to\infty\) as \(t\uparrow T<\infty\).",
    "informal_proof_text": "Define the variance \(V(t)=\int_{\mathbb{R}^d}|x|^2|u(t,x)|^2\,dx\ge 0\). By the virial identity (node: virial_identity), \(V''(t)=16E(u_0)<0\). Hence \(V\) is a strictly concave quadratic in \(t\) with negative leading coefficient; since \(V\ge 0\), there exists a finite time \(T>0\) at which \(V(T)=0\) and \(V(t)\to 0\) as \(t\uparrow T\). By the weighted \(L^2\) inequality (node: weighted_l2_ineq) applied to \(f=u(t)\) and mass conservation, \(M^2=\|u_0\|_{L^2}^2\le \frac{2}{d}\sqrt{V(t)}\,\|\nabla u(t)\|_{L^2}\). As \(\sqrt{V(t)}\to 0\) while \(M>0\) is fixed, we obtain \(\|\nabla u(t)\|_{L^2}\to\infty\). Since \(\|u(t)\|_{L^2}=M\) is conserved, \(\|u(t)\|_{H^1}^2=M^2+\|\nabla u(t)\|_{L^2}^2\to\infty\).",
    "display_label": "Glassey Blow-up"
  },
  {
    "id": "virial_identity",
    "title": "Virial Identity: \(V''(t)=16E(u(t))\)",
    "informal_statement": "For any sufficiently regular solution of the focusing mass-critical NLS, the variance \(V(t)=\int_{\mathbb{R}^d}|x|^2|u(t,x)|^2\,dx\) satisfies\n\[\nV''(t)=8\int_{\mathbb{R}^d}|\nabla u|^2\,dx-\frac{16}{2+4/d}\int_{\mathbb{R}^d}|u|^{2+4/d}\,dx=16E(u(t)).\n\]",
    "informal_proof_text": "Differentiate \(V(t)=\int|x|^2|u|^2\,dx\) once using \(u_t=i\Delta u+i|u|^{4/d}u\): the nonlinear term drops out (it is real, multiplied by \(i\)), giving\n\[\nV'(t)=4\operatorname{Im}\int_{\mathbb{R}^d}x\cdot\nabla u\,\overline{u}\,dx.\n\]\nDifferentiate again. Decompose into linear and nonlinear contributions.\n\n**Linear part**: A two-step integration by parts with the Laplacian gives\n\[\n4\operatorname{Re}\int x\cdot\nabla\Delta u\,\overline{u}\,dx-4\operatorname{Re}\int x\cdot\nabla u\,\Delta\overline{u}\,dx=8\int|\nabla u|^2\,dx.\n\]\n**Nonlinear part**: Using \(\nabla(|u|^{4/d}u)\,\overline{u}=\nabla\!\left(\tfrac{d}{2d+4}|u|^{2+4/d}\right)+|u|^{4/d}\nabla u\,\overline{u}\), the two nonlinear terms combine to\n\[\n4\int x\cdot\nabla\!\left(\tfrac{d}{2d+4}|u|^{2+4/d}\right)dx.\n\]\nIntegrating by parts with \(\operatorname{div}(x)=d\) yields \(-\tfrac{16}{2+4/d}\int|u|^{2+4/d}\,dx\).\n\nHence\n\[\nV''(t)=8\int|\nabla u|^2\,dx-\frac{16}{2+4/d}\int|u|^{2+4/d}\,dx=16E(u(t)).\n\]\nBy energy conservation, \(E(u(t))=E(u_0)\) for all \(t\).",
    "display_label": "Virial Identity"
  },
  {
    "id": "weighted_l2_ineq",
    "title": "Weighted \(L^2\) Inequality",
    "informal_statement": "For sufficiently regular \(f:\mathbb{R}^d\to\mathbb{C}\),\n\[\n\|f\|_{L^2(\mathbb{R}^d)}^2\le\frac{2}{d}\,\|xf\|_{L^2(\mathbb{R}^d)}\,\|\nabla f\|_{L^2(\mathbb{R}^d)}.\n\]",
    "informal_proof_text": "Write\n\[\n\|f\|_{L^2}^2=\int|f|^2\,dx=\frac{1}{d}\int(\operatorname{div}x)|f|^2\,dx=-\frac{1}{d}\int x\cdot\nabla(|f|^2)\,dx=-\frac{2}{d}\operatorname{Re}\int x\cdot\nabla f\,\overline{f}\,dx.\n\]\nApplying \(|\operatorname{Re}z|\le|z|\) and Cauchy–Schwarz:\n\[\n\|f\|_{L^2}^2\le\frac{2}{d}\left|\int x\cdot\nabla f\,\overline{f}\,dx\right|\le\frac{2}{d}\,\|xf\|_{L^2}\,\|\nabla f\|_{L^2}.\n\]",
    "display_label": "Weighted \(L^2\) Ineq."
  }
]","edges":"[
  {
    "source_id": "virial_identity",
    "target_id": "root",
    "label": "provides \(V''(t)=16E(u_0)<0\)",
    "explanation": "The virial identity gives the key ODE for \(V\); negativity of energy forces \(V\) to reach zero in finite time."
  },
  {
    "source_id": "weighted_l2_ineq",
    "target_id": "root",
    "label": "forces \(\|\nabla u\|\to\infty\) as \(V\to 0\)",
    "explanation": "Applied with \(f=u(t)\) and mass conservation, the weighted inequality turns \(V(t)\to 0\) into \(\|\nabla u(t)\|_{L^2}\to\infty\)."
  }
]","candidates":"[
